(Translated by Google) So far, the opinions on the Waffle House divide and that applies to pretty much any location. We were also put off for a long time. But at some point then decided: we test it yourself!  Since then we may not be the biggest fans, but once on vacation we go to breakfast in a Waffle House.  There are not only waffles, but you get other things for breakfast. Lunch and dinner are also offered. The special feature is: you can eat all dishes at all times of the day.  The decor is reminiscent of many diners from films. In the middle you will find the counter with bar stools, behind the open kitchen. On the right side there are tables / chairs / niches / benches or similar. Overall, it is rather small.  Here you can see in any case how everything is prepared and how clean worked (or not).  Service was fast, nice and friendly. By the way, you do not pay directly at the service, but you get your bill and go to the counter.  There were three of us there and ordered quite different things. Waffle, hashbrowns, cheesesteak sandwich ...  The Hashbrowns I find here delicious (reminiscent of our Rösti). You get them pure, or with various side dishes. For example, Onions, cheese, ham, tomatoes, jalapenos, chili, mushrooms, sausage gravy ...  Otherwise there are also burgers and steaks, which we have not tried. As I said, for us that is more of a breakfast location. Whereby also established men already eat a steak for breakfast.  All in all, it tastes and pleases us well and therefore: on the next holiday again, even if it is then another branch.  The restrooms I would have liked a little bit cleaner and fragrant, the drain has unfortunately very intense stewed.  (Original) So weit gehen die Meinungen zum Waffle House auseinander und das trifft auf ziemlich jede Location zu. Wir haben uns auch lange abschrecken lassen. Aber irgendwann dann doch mal entschieden: Wir testen es doch selber!  Seither sind wir vielleicht nicht die allergrößten Fans, aber einmal im Urlaub gehen wir doch zum Frühstück in ein Waffle House.  Hier gibt es aber nicht nur Waffeln, sondern man bekommt noch andere Sachen zum Frühstück. Lunch und Dinner wird auch angeboten. Das Besondere ist: Man kann alle Gerichte zu allen Tageszeiten essen.  Die Einrichtung erinnert an viele Diner aus Filmen. In der Mitte findet man die Theke mit Barhockern, dahinter die offene Küche. Rechts an den Seiten sind dann noch Tische/Stühle/Nischen/Bänke o.ä. Insgesamt ist es eher klein.  Hier sieht man auf jeden Fall wie alles zubereitet wird und wie sauber gearbeitet wird (oder eben nicht).  Service war schnell, nett und freundlich. Man zahlt hier übrigens nicht direkt bei der Bedienung, sondern bekommt seine Rechnung hingelegt und geht dann vor zum Tresen.  Wir sind zu dritt dort gewesen und haben ganz verschiede Sachen bestellt. Waffel, Hashbrowns, Cheesesteak-Sandwich...  Die Hashbrowns finde ich hier mega lecker (erinnert an unsere Rösti). Man bekommt sie pur, oder mit diversen Beilagen. Z.B. Zwiebeln, Käse, Schinken, Tomaten, Jalapenos, Chili, Pilze, Sausage Gravy...  Ansonsten gibt es auch noch Burger und Steaks, die wir noch nicht probiert haben. Wie gesagt, für uns ist das eher eine Frühstücks-Location. Wobei hier auch gestandene Männer schon ein Steak zum Frühstück vertilgen.  Insgesamt schmeckt und gefällt es uns auf jeden Fall gut und von daher: Im nächsten Urlaub wieder, auch wenn es dann eine andere Filiale ist.  Die Restrooms hätte ich mir ein klein wenig sauberer und wohlriechender gewünscht, der Abfluss hat leider sehr intensiv gemüffelt.

Love the waffles, but the wait staff in both Cape Coral locations suck!  The staff the one on DelPrado and 46th try but still need some polishing.  The young man who usually sits people on the weekend needs to not do major cleaning while customers are eating.  Last visit he was cleaning ceiling vents/tiles on a Saturday morning with the restaurant full.  Don't think anyone would appreciate that stuff falling into their food.  So I decided to try the one further north on DelPrado.  When I walk in a waitress calls out for me to sit where ever I want, there's just 1 empty booth and all the chairs towards the end of the counter are upside down on the counter.  This usually suggest the area is closed so I head to the booth.  It's dirty, food and napkins on the floor and syrup on the table.  I ask for someone to at least wipe off the table.  As soon as I sit, my waitress appears, (an older woman, 50+)..pad in hand, "what can I get you"?  Well... for starters..how about a menu?!   She reaches over to the counter a places a menu sticky with syrup in front of me.  Stands there while I look over the menu, I give her my order, peel the menu off the table and hand it back to her.  The table is now sticky again!  Another waitress wipes the table down again leaving it soaking wet.  I give up on getting a properly cleaned table.  My food arrives quickly, before the table dries, and my waitress puts it down and continues to walk away.  Guess what!  NO SILVERWARE, NO SYRUP !! As my food gets cold from the AC blowing full blast ( the condensation is just dripping down the windows), I try to get her attention.  No luck so I actually go behind the counter where I noticed the silverware is stored and help myself to a set and Dear Lord a bottle covered in syrup.  Now my waitress happens to be the person who rings me up and the look on her face when I didn't tip.  I told her she was old enough to know how to give proper service and I shook my head as I walked away.  Both Cape Coral Waffle Houses needs a training class for the wait staff.
